column1: For coding genes, we examined whether they are supported by UniProt annotation (“evidence at the protein level"), GO annotation (GO terms corresponding to experimental evidence codes including: TAS, IPI, IDA, EXP, IMP, IC, IEP and IGI), proteogenomics (at least two uniquely mapping spectra) and various Ka/Ks tests (significant or not). “1” and "NA" means the precense and absence of evidence, respectively.
